import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    job_counts = data.groupby('job')['count'].sum()
    job_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of job types in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    gender_counts = data.groupby('sex')['count'].sum()
    plt.pie(gender_counts, labels=gender_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the gender distribution in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    unique_jobs = data['job'].unique()
    for job in unique_jobs:
        job_data = data[data['job'] == job]
        plt.plot(job_data['year'], job_data['count'], label=job)
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the trend of job types over the years?')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    pivot_data = data.pivot_table(index='job', columns='sex', values='perc', aggfunc='sum')
    pivot_data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, ax=plt.gca())
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the percentage distribution of job types by gender?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    yearly_job_count = data.groupby('year')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(yearly_job_count['year'], yearly_job_count['count'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the overall trend of job count over the years?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
